605
00:37:48,347 --> 00:37:50,106
The two articles you wrote
are excellent.

606
00:37:50,987 --> 00:37:52,226
When the newspaper is out,

607
00:37:52,467 --> 00:37:54,186
they'll be
among the year's best articles.

608
00:37:54,626 --> 00:37:56,947
Alright, stop joking around
and get back to work.

609
00:37:57,666 --> 00:37:58,747
It's late. I'm leaving now.

610
00:37:58,747 --> 00:37:59,247
Okay.

611
00:39:03,066 --> 00:39:03,566
Hello?

612
00:39:03,907 --> 00:39:06,066
Hello, may I speak to Mr. Zheng?

613
00:39:08,066 --> 00:39:08,907
Hold on a moment.

614
00:39:12,106 --> 00:39:14,706
Mr. Zheng, your phone call.

615
00:39:15,347 --> 00:39:15,987
Okay, coming.

616
00:39:23,186 --> 00:39:24,120
Hello, who is this?

617
00:39:24,467 --> 00:39:25,026
Mr. Zheng.

618
00:39:25,907 --> 00:39:27,026
Mr. Zheng, it's Changyuan.

619
00:39:27,666 --> 00:39:28,827
Changyuan, what's up?

620
00:39:29,226 --> 00:39:31,026
Listen, I'm at the newspaper office now.

621
00:39:31,026 --> 00:39:32,506
I saw the articles about Yuehai.

622
00:39:33,787 --> 00:39:34,307
Articles?

623
00:39:35,267 --> 00:39:35,907
What articles?

624
00:39:36,987 --> 00:39:38,787
Mr. Zheng, I'm not flattering you.

625
00:39:38,907 --> 00:39:40,026
You're really amazing.

626
00:39:40,347 --> 00:39:41,387
Mr. Du

627
00:39:41,387 --> 00:39:43,546
gave two full pages to Yuehai.

628
00:39:43,706 --> 00:39:44,546
Let me read it.

629
00:39:45,626 --> 00:39:50,467
The title is "No Land Sales.
What's Next for Yuehai?"

630
00:39:53,106 --> 00:39:54,787
Okay, I see.

631
00:40:02,947 --> 00:40:05,626
Mr. Du is going to
publish those two articles.

632
00:40:05,947 --> 00:40:06,546
What?

633
00:40:07,546 --> 00:40:09,787
I haven't stamped them yet.
How can he publish them?

634
00:40:10,307 --> 00:40:12,024
Qian Changyuan
is in the provincial capital.

635
00:40:12,347 --> 00:40:15,267
He saw the press proof at the printery
for the New City Life newspaper.

636
00:40:15,787 --> 00:40:16,920
It hits the stands tonight.

637
00:40:21,867 --> 00:40:23,867
I need to go find Mr. Du in person.

638
00:40:24,307 --> 00:40:25,506
It's on the press.

639
00:40:25,626 --> 00:40:28,347
Even if you go to Du Tao now,
the articles can't be pulled back.

640
00:40:28,467 --> 00:40:29,506
We have to pull them back.

641
00:40:30,987 --> 00:40:31,747
I'll see Mr. Zhao.

642
00:40:33,146 --> 00:40:34,907
Provincial newspapers
are beyond his reach.

643
00:40:35,706 --> 00:40:36,987
I'll go to provincial leaders.

644
00:40:37,347 --> 00:40:38,947
Like Mr. Zhang. He helped us before.

645
00:40:39,467 --> 00:40:41,226
The two articles can't be published.

646
00:40:42,267 --> 00:40:42,947
Leave it to me.

647
00:40:43,987 --> 00:40:44,626
Mr. Zheng,

648
00:40:45,267 --> 00:40:47,586
we should report it
to Mr. Zhao at the county first.

649
00:40:48,947 --> 00:40:49,467
Good point.

650
00:40:50,226 --> 00:40:50,747
But...

651
00:40:51,066 --> 00:40:53,387
Then we'll split up.
I'll go to the county to see Mr. Zhao.

652
00:40:53,546 --> 00:40:55,226
You, the provincial capital.
We meet there.

653
00:40:55,666 --> 00:40:56,827
Alright. Thank you.

654
00:40:59,986 --> 00:41:01,467
